Mobileye4.1
Practical Engineer for Assembly Team
Jerusalem
Apply on employer site
Which department will you join?
The assembly department is responsible for assembling all the company's products.
We receive kits for assemblies from the Mobileye warehouse and at the end of the process we release complex and tested products to the following stations.
In our department, an acceptance test is performed for hardware received from suppliers (QAT).
We provide hardware repair support to all Mobileye Lab employees and external customers (RMA).
We provide support for prototypes of systems in development.

All you need is:

  • Degree in Practical Engineering in Electronics and Computers
  • Two years of experience in the field of computer hardware and assembling complex systems
  • Knowledge of acceptance tests of electronic boards
  • Ability to disassemble and assemble complex assemblies and test them
  • Rapid learning ability
  • Ability to write an email in English
  • Ability to work in a team
Mobileye changes the way we drive, from preventing accidents to semi and fully autonomous vehicles. If you are an excellent, bright, hands-on person with a passion to make a difference come to lead the revolution!
